==English==
===Etymology===
From Yiddish [[שמאָק]] ''shmok'', literally ''[[penis]]'' (''vulgar''), from Old Polish [[smok]] (modern Polish: [[smok]], ''dragon)''.

=== Noun ===
'''shmuck''' or '''schmuck'''
# ([[pejorative]])([[vulgar]]) of or relating to the [[penis]]
# a [[derogatory]] description of an individual (usually a man)
# a name used to [[describe]] a man who will insult you when you are down
